      "message": "(this comment is addressable in a followup CL)\nThis violates a few testing best practices making this harder to reason about than I would like.\n1) tests should be clear go/unit-test-practices#goals\n2) tests should contain as little logic as possible go/tott/510\n3) tests can be a bit less DRY than standard code go/tott/598\n\nFor me to figure out what CONTENT_FAIL/CONTENT_PASS... are, I have to mentally compute one or two Sprintfs. \n\nIt would be much better if you just had them hardcoded as strings. You can still have expected consts (PackageName, FailText, PassText, etc), but don\u0027t Sprintf them into the code under test.",
