      "message": "This is very hard for me to look at and know the test is doing the right thing. go/tott/598 recommends avoiding loops like this for that reason.\n\nI think it would be more clear and only a little repetitive if this loop were unrolled and the code looked like:\n\nrootStep :\u003d res\nrequire.Equal(t, rootStep, \"fake-test-task\")\nrequire.Len(t, rootStep.Steps, 1)\n\ntestStep :\u003d rootStep.Steps[0]\nrequire.Equal(t, testStep, \"go test --json ./...\")\n...\nrequire.Empty(t, thirdNestStep.Steps)",
